items.name: 526's Cusp of Serenity
items.description:
Disclaimer: This model is a little out-of-control. But dammit, I love it to death. It's intentionally kind of unhinged, and loves creating colorful, dreamlike, surreal illustrations. Don't use this model expecting a strong general-purpose experience. I can't make any guarantee that this model will be clean and coherent. This model was a creative exploration with the goal of a certain strong vibe and wacky creativity, not raw power and cleanliness. Leans a good bit towards its own illustrative style, so alternative styles may be trickier.

To get the full power of this model's creativity, I strongly recommend limiting your negative prompting as much as reasonably possible. You can use the bad-artist negative embedding to achieve certain effects, but beyond that embedding, I don't condone a lot else unless you are very sure of what you're doing.

If you're still interested by this model, read on.

SOME USAGE TIPS AND INFO:

  • I recommend keeping CFG around 7 and below. 5-7 is always a safe bet.

  • All my images were generated with 30 steps DDIM and upscaled via img2img at 0.47 strength (High Res Optimization, for InvokeAI users). You may need more steps if you aren't upscaling through that method.

  • Put in OliDisco style at the start of your prompt for interesting, trippy effect. Works best on vague as well as short prompts.

  • To kill unprompted extra random colors, put rainbow in your negative prompt, and weight as needed.

  • To kill the light glowing effect, put backlighting in your negative prompt, and weight as needed.

  • You can also try triggering the small portion of flat illustration LoRA with flat illustration in your prompt, the Vector Graphics Art Style LoRA with flat color in your prompt, and the Dreamy Vector Style LoRA with vectorstyle. Note those LoRAs were mainly used to enforce a style, but you can still get interesting effects with them.

MODEL BACKGROUND:

This model was based off of my 526Mix-Animated mix. While I would have loved to use my trusty ol' 526Mix, the Animated version has better lighting introduced by Nerfgun3's Macaron Mix that I felt would be more in line with the effects I wanted.

To create this model, I merged a bunch of LoRAs on top of 526Mix-Animated. This was done in two parts, with the goal of expanding on 526Mix/526Mix-Animated's natural creativity, while creating some nice cozy and thoughtful vibes.

Full credits to the authors of these LoRAs, and I suggest using them on their own to get their full powers.

Part 1:

  • AlchemistW's Enhanced Backlighting at 0.40 multiplier

  • IronCat's Anime vibrancy & simplifier at 0.40 multiplier

  • TLME's Vector Graphics Art Style (No lineart) at 0.80 multiplier

  • olivetty's Soul of Disco Diffusion at 0.60 multiplier

This model made stunningly bright and colorful illustrations, but was often a bit too saturated.

Part 2:

  • AlchemistW's Enhanced Backlighting at 0.50 multiplier

  • l616631804190's flat illustration at 0.65 multiplier

  • olivetty's Soul of Disco Diffusion at 0.60 multiplier

  • The_Jingo's Cosmic Rainbow at 0.25 multiplier

  • Gertan's Dreamy Vector Style at 0.50 multiplier

Parts 1 and 2 were then mixed at a 50/50 ratio to balance each other's quirks.

Judging by the time I typed 'that dumb LoRA has me wanting to make an unhinged surrealist model...' in the InvokeAI discord server, total experimentation time was about 11 hours, not including the several hours of pre-exploration before going through on the idea for this model.

items.name: T800 Terminator Endoskeleton
items.description:
After scouring through hundreds of models and trying to generate a Terminator Endoskeleton it became obvious to me that very little of Terminator exists in any model's training data. So, using Hollowstraberry's tutorial & colab I trained this LORA on about 80 HD images at about 4000 steps on Experience 8.0. It does closeups the best, but full body shots are still quite good, and seems quite flexible with styles and different models.

I recommend a weight of 0.8 - 0.9

Adding "holding a gun" or "holding a futuristic gun shooting lasers" without quotations should produce the signature futuristic rifle the Terminators usually use in the future.

I recommend 512x512 or 768, LORA was trained at 768 resolution so does well with higher resolution. It seems to handle high res fix really well and produces amazing quality with it.

This is my second LORA and I don't really know what I'm doing outside of the tutorial and colab, I have a AMD 7900xt so I have to use the DirectML version of A1111 whichi doesn't currently work for local training for me. If there's any tips you might have, please let me know.

Please rate & comment and share your generations & let me know how I'm doing!

Please consider supporting me so I can continue to make more Models / LoRA's for the community! --> Buy Me A Coffee

In my pursuit of training a new Furry model I've begun to produce new loRA's, in preparation for creating a more varied, cohesive database from which to work off of.

This model handles both Feral and Anthro variants rather well. Also, the tags might be a bit strong on this one, so you might want to turn down the strength of the LoRA depending on what you're going for. Using the weights at 0.4 seems to work best for more varied results.

This LoRA was trained using Furry Vixens 2.0, and works exceptionally well with it! The images were generated using clip skip 2.

Eevee, Eevee tail, Eevee ears, brown eyes, brown fur, autumn, forest, trees

This Lora is trained on the cute artworks of Kionant (NFSW Artist), mostly known for drawing monster girls, and pokemons, if you're interested make sure to check his work or Twitter or Instagram .

Usage Tips :

  • Experiment with adding kionant to the prompt to feather anchor the style.

  • This LoRA will try to make make the proportions super stylized, if you dont want it to have a strong affect on the shapes use with weight lower then 0.75.

  • elf ears, solved by adding pointy ears to the Negative prompt.

items.name: IronCatLoRA #6 - Genos | One Punch Man
items.description:
IronCatLoRA #6 - Genos | One Punch Man

Making LoRA's is a thing I do for fun. So if you like what I do? You can help me out by just using the LoRA and leaving a review!

This time I present to you a character LoRA for Genos from One Punch Man. I like One Punch Man quite a bit. I especially think Genos is quite the badass. I noticed that there was also was no Genos LoRA to be found on CivitAI, so I just had to make it. I hope you're able to make badass images with Genos too, just like I was!

A weight around 0.8 for this LoRA seems optimal, usage may vary. From my testing a weight of 0.7 to 1.0 seemed to work good. Example images I've uploaded are mostly using 0.8. I've used YesMix for all the main example images, since in my own opinion it compliments Genos' look really nice (yeah kinda strange model for Genos, but I make big testing grids with multiple checkpoints, it was just the way like he was glowing looked really good). I've also uploaded some images generated with ReV Animated, which seems to generate semi-realistic images with Genos really well.

The main trigger word is genos. I tried to make this LoRA as flexible as I could, because of that you have certain additional words you must use to get certain characteristics of Genos. You can take a look at the example images I've uploaded how to prompt him, but here is an overview as well:

  • mechanical arms, if you want to make sure he generates with his mechanical arms add this in your prompt. He will have them most of the times, but you can't go wrong by just adding it if you want his mechanical arms to be in the image.

    • You could also e.g. put it in the negative prompt so you can more easily prompt Genos with long sleeved clothing. Which may generate him with normal flesh hands, using mechanical hands may help then. Although usage may vary, as the dataset is not trained on mechanical hands.

  • topless male in combination with cyborg helps generating him where his cyborg torso is shown. The dataset this LoRA was trained on doesn't actually have a lot of image with him like this, and the ones that are in the dataset only have like upper torso and up. So the cyborg part is to make sure Genos isn't generated with a flesh torso. Although not totally lore accurate it looked good enough in my testing.

  • sleeveless, if you want to have his sleeveless look from the clothing he wears in the show you can add this to your prompt. Again same as the mechanical arms, can also work by putting it in the negative prompt for e.g. long sleeved clothing.

  • The following prompts will generate him with clothing he is known to wear: blue shirt, white shirt, black pants, hood, hoodie, grey shirt, jeans & boots.

  • The following prompts will generate him with his cyborg body glowing: glowing, glowing eyes & glowing hand. You can use them together or just pick the one(s) you want.

    • glowing hand might be a hit or miss, because hands and stable diffusion... It will try to attempt the hand beam pose.

  • fighting stance, the dataset this LoRA has been trained on has Genos in various fighting poses. This prompt generates him in certain stances. Also including standing may force him in a standing fighting stance.

    • clenched hand may also help generate an image where is is clenching his hand in a fighting stance.

  • floating hair may also sometimes work to generate him where his hair is blown back, like e.g. in the show when he was training with Saitama.

  • It seems the LoRA is also flexible enough to genderbend Genos, if you're into that... It seems just prompting that Genos has breasts, does the trick. I've also uploaded some example images regarding this.
